00:00:00.630 --> 00:00:02.850
A line goes through
the following points,

00:00:02.850 --> 00:00:06.890
and the equation of that line
is written in y equals mx plus b

00:00:06.890 --> 00:00:07.390
form.

00:00:07.390 --> 00:00:09.890
Also known as
slope-intercept form.

00:00:09.890 --> 00:00:11.880
What is the equation
of the line?

00:00:11.880 --> 00:00:13.630
So the first thing we
want to think about,

00:00:13.630 --> 00:00:14.990
what is the slope of this line?

00:00:14.990 --> 00:00:16.530
What is m here?

00:00:16.530 --> 00:00:20.020
So what is our change in
y for given change in x?

00:00:20.020 --> 00:00:21.915
So this is an
interesting example here.

00:00:21.915 --> 00:00:24.540
And I encourage you to pause the
video and try it out yourself.

00:00:24.540 --> 00:00:28.150
Because no matter how much we
change x, y is not changing.

00:00:28.150 --> 00:00:30.350
y is a constant, 2.

00:00:30.350 --> 00:00:33.476
So your change in y between any
two points is going to be 0.

00:00:33.476 --> 00:00:35.100
It doesn't matter
what your change in x

00:00:35.100 --> 00:00:38.690
is, your change in x could be
1, your change in x could be 4,

00:00:38.690 --> 00:00:40.740
your change in y is always 0.

00:00:40.740 --> 00:00:43.690
So y is not changing
as you change x.

00:00:43.690 --> 00:00:48.660
So your slope for this
relationship is actually 0.

00:00:48.660 --> 00:00:52.700
Y is equal to 0x
plus-- and then, you

00:00:52.700 --> 00:00:55.740
could just realize that
the equation of this

00:00:55.740 --> 00:00:58.030
is just that y is
always equal to 2.

00:00:58.030 --> 00:01:02.730
So it's 0x plus 2, which is the
same thing as y is equal to 2.

00:01:02.730 --> 00:01:04.120
You could substitute back in.

00:01:04.120 --> 00:01:08.130
You could say OK, well, if
y is equal to 0x plus b,

00:01:08.130 --> 00:01:11.100
that means that y is equal to b.

00:01:11.100 --> 00:01:16.000
Well, y is always equal to 2,
no matter what thing you pick,

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:17.660
so b is equal to 2.

00:01:17.660 --> 00:01:20.400
So either way, this
just boils down to y

00:01:20.400 --> 00:01:24.340
is equal to 0x plus 2,
or y is just equal to 2.

00:01:24.340 --> 00:01:26.980
Let's do another one of these.

00:01:26.980 --> 00:01:28.890
Maybe one where the y
is actually changing.

00:01:28.890 --> 00:01:33.180
So here, the y is clearly
actually changing.

