00:02:12.970 --> 00:02:15.310
So what is our change in x here?

00:02:15.310 --> 00:02:18.950
So our change in x here, if we
go from 4 to 7, our change in x

00:02:18.950 --> 00:02:19.575
is equal to 3.

00:02:22.170 --> 00:02:24.510
And what's our change in y here?

00:02:24.510 --> 00:02:26.620
So we went up from 4 to 7.

00:02:26.620 --> 00:02:28.100
We increased by 3.

00:02:28.100 --> 00:02:30.470
Our y decreased by 2.

00:02:30.470 --> 00:02:32.800
Change in y is
equal to negative 2.

00:02:32.800 --> 00:02:37.580
So our slope, which is equal to
change in y over change in x,

00:02:37.580 --> 00:02:40.851
is equal to negative 2/3.

00:02:40.851 --> 00:02:42.850
And if you wanted to
relate that to the formulas

00:02:42.850 --> 00:02:44.260
that you normally
see for slope, you're

00:02:44.260 --> 00:02:45.551
just looking at your end point.

00:02:45.551 --> 00:02:49.370
So this is y2 minus
y1, which is negative 2

00:02:49.370 --> 00:02:52.780
over x2 minus x1,
which is 7 minus 4.

00:02:52.780 --> 00:02:55.520
But that just boils
down to negative 2/3.

00:02:55.520 --> 00:02:59.540
And so our equation is going
to be y is equal to negative

00:02:59.540 --> 00:03:03.920
